<div id='communityQuestionsWithAnswers'>
<div class='communityQuestionAndAnswer'>
<div class='communityQuestion'>
<div class='questionText'>
<a href="/questions/2033164-bertrand-russell-often-clarified-his">?Bertrand Russell Often clarified his position as agnosticism, and would probably not be impressed with the Atheism of today. I am not asking a question, just pointing this out, because goodreads decided to promote this book to me along with their misguiding description. I have read this and most of Russell&#39;s work already.</a>
</div>
<div class='communityQAFooter questionFooter'>
<ul class='questionFooterActions'>
<li class='footerItem like'>
<span class='likeItContainer' id='like_container_community_question_2033164'><a rel="nofollow" class="jsLike like_it" href="https://www.goodreads.com/user/new?remember=true&amp;return_url=%2Fbook%2Fshow%2F67354.What_I_Believe">like</a></span>

</li>
<li class='footerItem communityQuestionTimestamp'>
<a href="/questions/2033164-bertrand-russell-often-clarified-his">5 months ago</a>
</li>
<li class='footerItem communityQuestionPermalink'>
<a href="/questions/2033164-bertrand-russell-often-clarified-his">See all 2 answers</a>
</li>
</ul>
</div>

</div>
<div class='allCommunityAnswers'>
<div class='communityAnswer'>
<div class='communityAnswerBody'>
<div class='answererUserIcon'>
<a class="leftAlignedImage userPhoto" href="/user/show/47455316-borders-are-global-apartheid"><img alt="" src="https://i.gr-assets.com/images/S/compressed.photo.goodreads.com/users/1626651116i/47455316._UX100_CR0,0,100,100_.jpg" /></a>
</div>
<div class='communityAnswerTextContainer'>
<span class='communityAnswererName'>
<a href="/user/show/47455316-borders-are-global-apartheid">Borders Are Global Apartheid</a>
</span>
<span class='communityAnswerText'>
<span class="expandableContainer"><span class="truncatedContent">He did not believe in god, so he was an atheist. Atheism and agnosticism are not incompatible. I think the confusion arises from people believing the <a class="jsShow showAction" href="#">…more</a></span><span class="fullContent">He did not believe in god, so he was an atheist. Atheism and agnosticism are not incompatible. I think the confusion arises from people believing the two are distinct positions. But there is really no incompatibility between "I do not believe god exists" and "the existence of god is unknowable".<a class="jsHide hideAction" href="#">(less)</a></span></span>
</span>
</div>
</div>
