              <span id="reviewTextContainer3974633238" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer17418298365682812142">“The good life is one inspired by love and guided by knowledge.”<br/><br/>I wish my brain had the capability of projecting a little hologram of Bertrand Russell reciting “What I Believe” every time someone questioned my atheism. That way I could yell, “RELEASE THE KRAKEN!” and then sit back and watch all the self-righteous sanctimony vaporize under the concentrated beam of Bertrand’s irrefutable acumen. <br/><br/>“...nature is neither good nor bad, and is not concerned to make us happy or unhappy. All such philosop</span>
  <span id="freeText17418298365682812142" style="display:none">“The good life is one inspired by love and guided by knowledge.”<br /><br />I wish my brain had the capability of projecting a little hologram of Bertrand Russell reciting “What I Believe” every time someone questioned my atheism. That way I could yell, “RELEASE THE KRAKEN!” and then sit back and watch all the self-righteous sanctimony vaporize under the concentrated beam of Bertrand’s irrefutable acumen. <br /><br />“...nature is neither good nor bad, and is not concerned to make us happy or unhappy. All such philosophies spring from self-importance, and are best corrected by a little astronomy.”</span>
