<span id="freeTextContainer6980426827615810956">My thoughts about the roles of faith and religion in mankind&apos;s life are opposite to Russell&apos;s, but reading this man always gives me a great joy. This book is mainly related to sources and methods for a good life. Russell thinks that the scientific education is the best weapon with which we can transform impulsive, fearful and timid children to loving, humanistic and courageous adults. Isn&apos;t that admirable: &quot;A good life is one inspired by love and guided by knowledge.&quot;</span>
  <span id="freeText6980426827615810956" style="display:none">My thoughts about the roles of faith and religion in mankind's life are opposite to Russell's, but reading this man always gives me a great joy. This book is mainly related to sources and methods for a good life. Russell thinks that the scientific education is the best weapon with which we can transform impulsive, fearful and timid children to loving, humanistic and courageous adults. Isn't that admirable: "A good life is one inspired by love and guided by knowledge."</span>
