        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer3561495563" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer11875039418169529492">Compelling essay by a charming, passionate intellectual :-) <br/><br/>Russell covers some of his basic beliefs about life, how to live it, and how deplorable Christianity (and other religions) are. <br/><br/>A lot of his views mirror mine -- so go figure I liked it! <br/><br/>... and some seem not entirely correct to me or just lacking in nuance 😜<br/><br/>--<br/><br/>&quot;The good life is one inspired by love and guided by knowledge.<br/><br/>Both are indefinitely extensible, so a better life can always be imagined&quot;<br/><br/>Amen. Lots of confusion can be waded throu</span>
  <span id="freeText11875039418169529492" style="display:none">Compelling essay by a charming, passionate intellectual :-) <br /><br />Russell covers some of his basic beliefs about life, how to live it, and how deplorable Christianity (and other religions) are. <br /><br />A lot of his views mirror mine -- so go figure I liked it! <br /><br />... and some seem not entirely correct to me or just lacking in nuance 😜<br /><br />--<br /><br />"The good life is one inspired by love and guided by knowledge.<br /><br />Both are indefinitely extensible, so a better life can always be imagined"<br /><br />Amen. Lots of confusion can be waded through when one tries to live entirely by knowledge.<br /><br />--<br /><br />The basic facts of sex should be taught before they are interesting, as well as instructions to wait for a safe opportunity with parental care available :-)<br /><br />-- <br /><br />"To have progress we must be dominated by hope, not fear."<br /><br />--<br /><br />He seems to agree with my split:<br /><br />a) Desires/values<br />b) Ethical policy to best satisfy (a)<br /><br />-- Love and Knowledge again.<br /><br />Next up is,<br /><br />c) Non-contradictory systems of desries are superior to contradictory ones.<br /><br />Thus Love &gt; Hate, for Hate is almost by definition going to run into desire conflicts! <br /><br />Ben G. is chugging on this topic under the heading, "coherent value systems": <a target="_blank" rel="noopener nofollow" href="http://multiverseaccordingtoben.blogspot.com/2020/06/foundations-of-coherent-value.html">http://multiverseaccordingtoben.blogs...</a><br /><br />--<br /><br />I recommend the essays to get a glimpse for how Russel thinks beyond Logicomix. </span>
  <a data-text-id="11875039418169529492" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


